gloss.term:
Not to be confused with Mahendra or Mahā­sena;
                                or with Mahendrasena, a future monarch of Kauśāmbī;
                                    Mahendrasena, the prince
                                of Potalaka; or Mahendrasena, the king of Vārāṇasī.

The name of the town where Kaineya lived;
                                traditionally spelled Udumā, the rendering in The Hundred Deeds may be derived from the Pāli/Prakṛt
                                form Ātumā.
